iron.service

These classes handle business logic. They perform actions and enforce rules in the system.

RaceService

Handles race creation and race management logic. This class would contain methods for creating races, updating race details, setting participant limits, and setting registration deadlines.

RegistrationService

Handles the process of registering racers for races. This class checks rules such as whether the race is official, whether the racer has a valid license, whether the racer matches the required category, and whether the participant limit has been reached.

CategoryUpgradeService

Handles category upgrade logic. This class checks race results to determine whether a racer is eligible for a category upgrade, such as after earning enough podium finishes.

LicenseService

Handles license-related operations. This may include issuing a license, renewing a license, checking expiration, and validating whether a racer can enter official races.

NotificationService

Handles sending notifications to racers. This class would be responsible for generating and delivering system messages based on important events.

ReviewService

Handles the creation and management of race reviews. This class can enforce rules such as whether only racers who participated in a race are allowed to submit a review.

ResultService

Handles race result submission and lookup. This class can be used by organizers to enter results and by the system to retrieve standings or podium information.